title: FLEXnet for AllData 10.53 hacks
description:
Thanks to trentofdestiny on suprbay for pointing out a bug and solution. His post and others can be found at:
 <a href="
https://forum.suprbay.org/Thread-AllData-10-53-Q3-2013-Last-DVD-set-EVER" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
https://forum.suprbay.org/Thread-AllData-10-53-Q3-2013-Last-DVD-set-EVER</a>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Extract into...

for WinXP:
C:UsersPublicApplication Data

for WinVista/7/8:
C:ProgramData


For use with AllData 10.53:

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
To disable the rearm of activation for ace.exe:
- Extract zip as shown above.
- Then in the start menu look for "software updates".
- Open FLEXnet Software Manager then let it load.
- Then look for AllData and set the updates to "manual" instead of "everyday at 12".
- There is no need to delete anything.
- You no longer have to worry about it rearming again. 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
